<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43320857" data-cid="43320857">
    <div id="comment_43320857">
        <header data-points="0" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:Basic summary:"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:Basic summary:<span> (0)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3598035&cid=43320857">(#43320857)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43320857" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="0" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>This is why most researchers clain that RF doesnt do anything:<br>This A-&gt;B (RF causes local heating).. and B-&gt;C (local heating causes disease) is both not significant.</p><p>But the mechanism of RF causing changes in cells could be very different.<br>They may have implications on biology that we have not researched well yet..</p><p>There are far more mechanisms than heating that may cause stress or damage to the biological body.<br>To name a few:<br>1) Resonating ions<br>The Cells, especially the nervous system is a complex system that contains all kinds of different ions and atoms contained within complex structures.<br>The ions may resonate with certain frequencies and break the boundaries of the structures it was contained in (more often than regular). For example this may give some stress on the nervous system.<br>This is what researchers have indeed found: People are more stressed under RF.<br>2) Resonating nucleus<br>As known the nucleus of an atom may resonate with certain high frequenies.<br>Small structures within cells (like DNA) are of such a small scale that building them takes a lot of mechanisms work together in harmony. The body prefers certain nucleus of the same atom over others, and certain chemical reactions are different depending on the amount of neutrons in the nucleus (like Ozone). Therefore there is some kind of interaction between the inside of the nucleus and the chemical constructions is certainly present. Even if this interaction is weak it is still possible that certain chemical reactions are influenced by resonating nucleus of atoms.<br>Researchers did find an increase in DNA breakage under some high frequencies, so therefore it is possible that the DNA itself may have chemical structures or reactions that are influenced by nucleus of the atoms.</p><p>Compared with background radiation of any kind, all artificial radiation is usually of a certain frequency. This means anything artificial RF may cause resonating, while the natural version does not.</p></div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_43320857">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3598035" data-cid="43320857">
                    <button class="btn btn-default call-form" data-sid="43320857" data-pid="43320857" data-cid="43320857"><i class="fa fa-reply"></i> Reply</button>
