        <article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43319899" data-cid="43319899">
    <div id="comment_43319899">
        <header data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:idiocy"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:idiocy<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3598035&cid=43319899">(#43319899)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43319899" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p><div class="quote"><p>Careful with the blanket safety statements there. Non-ionising radition includes things like UV light (sunburn at the beach, etc.)</p></div><p>To photo-ionize hydrogen, needs an energy of 13.6 eV. That energy corresponds to a wavelength of 91.2 nm. UV light ranged from 3 eV to 124 eV the equivalent of 400 nm to 10 nm. Ionizing radiation begins in the ultra violet. That's why sun light causes skin cancer. It's ionizing.</p></div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_43319899">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3598035" data-cid="43319899">
